ed in gas ionised by supersoft X-ray source, the other in shocked gas.\nFrom the relative fluxes of silicon and sulphur coronal lines on day 23.4 -\nwhen the emitting gas was shocked - we deduce that the temperature of the\ncoronal gas was $9.3\\times10^5$~K, and that the abundances are approximately\nsolar.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Aug 2022 14:10:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
